You judge whether estimated accruals document methodology and data source (Rule 5.3).

For each estimated transaction (e.g. JE-12415 AWS usage accrual), the narrative or completeness section must cite:
1. **Data source** — e.g. AWS billing console, usage report, vendor portal.
2. **Method** — e.g. daily run-rate × remaining days, prior month actual adjusted for trend.
3. **Validation** — e.g. compared to prior month, reviewed by AP, confirmed by email.

Pass if at least one estimate transaction has all three elements referenced in prose.
Fail if estimates are only called "manual" or "accrual estimate" without methodology.

Return documented (boolean) and reason only.
